Mr Shinde's comments on Tuesday came soon after Congress' Maharashtra President, Nana Patole, demanded the resignation of the chief minister and his deputies, claiming that there is a nexus between the police, politicians and the rich and influential people in the state.

snippet.description:
Pune Porsche Accident: Builder Allegedly Told Driver, To Let Teen Son Drive Porsche | Pune Accident
| Driver's Statement

In a recent development related to the fatal crash, Vishal Agarwal is alleged to have instructed the driver to allow his teenage son to drive the Porsche. Pune police, during their interrogation on Thursday, questioned several individuals involved in the accident, including the accused minor's grandfather, a friend, and the family driver. According to the driver's statement during questioning, he initially suggested driving, but Vishal insisted that his son take the wheel. The Pune Police commissioner noted discrepancies in the driver's initial claim of being behind the wheel and stated they are investigating the circumstances under which this statement was made. Recently, the accused minor asserted that the family driver was driving during the accident, a claim supported by his two friends and Vishal Agarwal himself.

snippet.title: Pune Porsche Accident | Teen's Grandfather Accused Of Pressuring The Driver To Take The Blame | N18V
snippet.description:
The grandfather of the 17-year-old, whose late-night drunken drive in a Porsche, left two young IT professionals dead in Pune, has been arrested for allegedly pressuring the family driver to take the blame for the accident. In his statement to police, the 42-year-old driver has said that soon after the incident, he received a call from the teen's grandfather. "He first called me up and shouted at me over the phone. Then, he forcibly took me to their bungalow in their BMW car," the driver has said. The teen's father and his grandfather snatched his mobile phone, he has said. The driver was confined to the bungalow. "I was told to take the blame. He told me, 'If you talk to anyone about this, remember...'," the driver has said. The teen's grandfather has now been arrested under charges of wrongful confinement, kidnapping and criminal intimidation.

snippet.title: Pune Porsche Accident: Pune Teen's Father Sent To Judicial Custody With 5 Others | Vishal Agarwal
snippet.description:
Pune Porsche Accident: Pune Teen's Father Sent To Judicial Custody With 5 Others | Vishal Agarwal

In a recent development, a special court in Pune has extended the judicial custody of Vishal Agarwal, the father of the minor accused of driving, along with five others until June 7. Agarwal maintains his innocence and claims to be falsely implicated. The Pune Police chief highlighted an attempt to tamper with evidence, indicating that the Porsche involved in the crash was driven by a family driver, not the detained 17-year-old. Additionally, Pune police revealed that Vishal instructed the driver to allow his son to drive the Porsche Taycan.
